article.description: Grant Riller had 24 points as College of Charleston topped Delaware 80-71 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Riller carries Coll. Of Charleston over Delaware 80-71
article.linkText: Riller carries Coll. Of Charleston over Delaware 80-71
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Grant Riller had 24 points as College of Charleston topped Delaware 80-71 on Thursday night. Brevin Galloway had 19 points for College of Charleston (16-13, 10-7 Colonial Athletic Association), which snapped its four-game losing streak. Sam Miller added 16 points and eight rebounds. College of Charleston totaled 52 points in the second half, a season high for the team. Justyn Mutts had 18 points and 11 rebounds for the Fightin' Blue Hens (20-10, 10-7). Nate Darling added 18 points. Ryan Allen had 12 points. The Cougars improve to 2-0 against the Fightin' Blue Hens on the season. College of Charleston defeated Delaware 75-63 on Dec. 30. College of Charleston finishes out the regular season against Drexel at home on Saturday. Delaware finishes out the regular season against UNC Wilmington on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
